8 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Process for appointing commissioners. (1) As provided in 69-1-103,
9 commissioners are to be appointed by the governor and confirmed by the senate.
10 (2) (a) An entity that is subject to regulation by the commission may not put forward candidate
11 suggestions to the governor for consideration. The governor is not obligated to choose a candidate
12 recommended by a regulated entity.
13 (b) Political parties, political committees, and political party committees may not put forward
14 candidate suggestions to the governor for consideration.
15 (3) The governor shall ensure that candidates meet the requirements provided in [section 5] before
16 announcing their nomination.
17 (4) (a) During the confirmation process, the senate shall confirm that the governor's assessment of
18 the candidates' qualifications is accurate. The senate may also explore the ethics and fitness for office of the
19 candidates.
20 (b) The senate may not refuse an appointment based on criteria not listed here or in [section 5].
21 The senate may not refuse an appointment because an industry, as defined in [section 5], is not represented,
22 so long as no industry is represented by two or more appointees.
23
